  In parallel, the drift ledger classifies the mixed-pattern items D1-D11 with severity, evidence, classification, downstream owner, and a local-vs-rewrite-scale boundary so S03/S04/S05 can normalize the right seams without redoing the audit. The ledger explicitly marks runtime bridge/wiring work as local drift and per-Digimon blueprint migration as follow-up-scale work. Finally, the slice added `scripts/verify_combat_authority_audit.py`, which makes the audit objective by checking requirement coverage, drift inventory, placeholder absence, and tracked-path references.
