### S03
[## What Happened] line 86: ## What Happened
  S03 consumed the S02 authority map and drift ledger and normalized the highest-risk local combat authority drift toward the agreed path `RON custom signals -> per-Digimon blueprint Rust module -> generic kernel hooks -> canonical state/events/snapshots`. The slice first repaired S03-owned test fixture drift without restoring obsolete Holy Support APIs (`Effect::HolySupportTag`, `Effect::HolySupportRequest`, or `TargetShape::SelfTarget`) and refreshed Twin Core tests onto the current hook-driven state vocabulary. It then made the kernel runtime participate in real headless paths by registering existing mechanic appliers for the app and combat CLI, while the action pipeline now emits live lifecycle `OnCombatBeat` and `OnKernelTransition::Beat` events directly from deterministic resolution.
  The new content seam is typed and data-only: `SkillDef` gained defaulted `custom_signals`, `assets/data/skills.ron` seeds `patamon_ult` with `Patamon(BuildHolySupportGrace(amount: 1))`, and `ResolvedAction` copies those custom signals from the resolved skill so downstream logic does not need asset re-lookups. `apply_effects` remains focused on ordinary effects and does not interpret per-Digimon behavior.
