### S05
[## What Happened] line 60: ## What Happened
  S05 repaired the combat CLI from a fragile smoke path into a deterministic real-binary proof of the shared combat architecture. The CLI now loads tracked RON assets through manifest-root helpers and Bevy `AssetPlugin.file_path`, so it works from a non-root cwd instead of relying on repository-root launch behavior. It waits for the real shared `SkillBook` asset and runtime data readiness rather than constructing an empty fallback book, which prevents proof output from hiding startup drift. Shared encounter bootstrap now inserts the `SpeedModifier(0)` invariant needed by the AV/turn-order systems, so first actor selection remains owned by shared combat systems rather than the CLI.
  An env-gated proof mode (`BEVYROGUE_CLI_PROOF=1`) was added to the actual `combat_cli` binary. In proof mode the binary disables prompts, waits for live ECS readiness, lets the shared action/query/turn-resolution/kernel/event systems run, captures a validation snapshot via `capture_validation_snapshot(world)`, prints `[CLI_PROOF] validation_snapshot: ...`, and exits deterministically via `AppExit`. Bounded failure cases now emit explicit `[CLI_PROOF] readiness_timeout:` or `[CLI_PROOF] validation_snapshot_error:` markers and become real process failures. This makes hidden startup drift observable instead of silently producing a misleading success.
[## Verification] line 70: ## Verification
  Fresh post-update verification passed in `gsd_exec` run `9634c05c-0758-48ea-a38b-e891d4bf6849`: `cargo test --test combat_cli_shared_surface --test presentation_metadata_boundary --test event_stream --test patamon_blueprint_seam` passed, `python3 scripts/verify_combat_authority_audit.py` passed, `python3 scripts/verify_m015_failure_ledger.py` passed, and `BEVYROGUE_JSONL=1 BEVYROGUE_CLI_PROOF=1 cargo run --bin combat_cli` passed with required shared-surface markers present and forbidden startup-drift markers absent. Earlier slice verification also passed in `78bc086c-6bb9-4d18-9183-96f62cfe1790` and `925a547f-6e28-4e8c-9f73-612cfeb3209a`. A security subagent review found no High/Critical blockers for the S05 file-IO/env/subprocess scope. Broad full-suite blockers remain intentionally S06-owned.
[## Deviations] line 95: ## Deviations
  The slice touched `src/combat/bootstrap.rs` to add the shared `SpeedModifier(0)` spawn invariant because the correct fix was in shared bootstrap, not CLI-only turn selection. `.gsd/PROJECT.md` was refreshed after S05 completion state and R098 validation. Reviewer/tester subagent attempts returned external usage-limit messages, but the security subagent completed with no High/Critical blockers and fresh local verification passed.
